The paper deals with the problem of autonomous mobile robots moving in the Euclidean plane, which is a classic topic in robotics and falls under the category of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves algorithms and computational complexity, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The problem of Near-Gathering involves coordination and cooperation among multiple robots, which falls under the category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also deals with the issue of termination detection, which is a key aspect of control systems and falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the use of algorithms to solve a problem, which suggests that it could also belong to the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI).
